==> First register the server to redhat
# subscription-manager register  >> provide redhat portal usernama and password

==> Ensure the server has a unique Fully Qualified Domain Name (FQDN) and proper DNS resolution (both forward and reverse).
==>Have active Red Hat subscriptions and manifests ready.
==>Check system requirements: minimum 4-core CPU, 20 GB RAM, sufficient disk space (depends on content and usage).
==>Configure necessary network ports and firewall rules
==> The enable the required repos baseos, appstream, satellite and satellite-maintenance
==> update the server
# dnf update -y

==> Install satellite package

==> run satellite-installter to configure it

# satellite-installer --scenario satellite \
--foreman-initial-organization "Your_Org" \
--foreman-initial-location "Your_Location" \
--foreman-initial-admin-username admin \
--foreman-initial-admin-password YourPassword

==> Once complete, access the Satellite Web UI via https://<Satellite_FQDN> and log in with the admin credentials.
==> Upload manifests from the Red Hat Customer Portal to start managing content and hosts.
